    "patch_code": "public String chompBalanced(char open, char close) throws SelectorParseException{\n    int start = -1;\n    int end = -1;\n    int depth = 0;\n    char last = 0;\n    Queue<Character> q = new LinkedList<>();\n    boolean hasNoClosingBracket = false;\n    \n    do {\n        if (isEmpty()) break;\n        \n        if(hasNoClosingBracket){ \n            throw new SelectorParseException(\"Unbalanced opening brackets\", 1);\n        }\n      \n        Character c = consume();\n     \n        q.add(c);\n        if ((int)last !=  34) {\n            \n            if (c.equals(String.valueOf(open))) {\n                depth++;\n                \n                if (start == -1)\n                    start = pos;\n            }\n            else if (c.equals(String.valueOf(close))) {\n               depth--;\n            }\n        }else if((int)c== 34){\n           hasNoClosingBracket = true; \n        }\n      \n        if (depth <= 0 && last!= 0) {\n          end = pos-1;\n        }\n      \n       \n        last = c;\n        if (!isExpectingAttributeValue()) {\n            if(!q.contains(String.valueOf(open))||\n                !q.contains(String.valueOf(close))) {\n              end=pos;\n             }\n        }\n        \n        if(depth<0&&(int)last ==34){\n            start = pos;\n        }\n        \n    } while (depth >=0 );\n    \n    \n    String rVal = (end >0 ) ? queue.substring(start, end) : \"\";\n    \n    return rVal;\n    \n}",
