    "patch_code": "public String chompBalanced(char open, char close) throws ParserException {\n    int start = -1;\n    int end = -1;\n    int depth = 0;\n    char last = 0;\n    boolean wasOpen = false;\n\n    do {\n        if (isEmpty()) break;\n        Character c = consume();\n        if (last == 0 || last != ESC){\n            if (c.equals(open)){ \n                depth++;\n                wasOpen = true;\n                if (start == -1)\n                    start = pos;\n            } else if (c.equals(close)){\n                if (!wasOpen) throw new SelectorParseException(\"Unbalanced \" + open + \"/\"+close,\"\");\n                wasOpen = false;\n                depth--;\n                \n            }\n\n            if (depth > 0 && last != 0 )\n                end = pos; // don't include the outer match pair in the return\n            \n        }else{\n          wasOpen = false;  \n        }\n        last = c;\n    }while (depth>0);\n    \n    \n    if (depth<0) throw new SelectorParseException (\"unexpected closing \" + close,\"\");\n\n    return (end>= 0)? queue.substring(start,end) : \"\";\n}",
